Reasoning: The paper deals with physical layer security in wireless communication systems, which is a topic that falls under the intersection of several CS sub-disciplines. However, based on the content of the abstract, the most likely sub-category is cs.IT (Information Theory), as the paper focuses on optimizing power allocation and sub-carrier assignment to maximize the end-to-end secrecy rate. The paper also deals with relay-assisted transmission, which suggests that it could belong to cs.NI (Networking and Internet Architecture) or cs.CR (Cryptography and Security). Additionally, the use of OFDM and the high SNR approximation suggest that the paper could also belong to cs.SY (Systems and Control) or cs.MM (Multimedia).
